
[1]conjoin

   CONJOIN, v.t. [L., to join. See Join.]

   1. To join together, without any thing intermediate; to unite two or
   more persons or things in close connection; as, to conjoin friends; to
   conjoin man and woman in marriage.

   2. To associate, or connect.

   Let that which he learns next be nearly conjoined with what he knows
   already.

                 CONJOIN, v.i. To unite; to join; to league.
